com.trigersoft.jaque.expression

Class Expression

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.trigersoft.jaque.expression.Expression
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConstantExpression, InvocableExpression, InvocationExpression, ParameterExpression, UnaryExpression

    public abstract class Expression
extends Object
    Provides the base class from which the classes that represent expression tree nodes are derived. It also contains static factory methods to create the various node types.
    Author:
    Konstantin Triger

                                   Expression ifTrue,
                                   Expression ifFalse)

        Parameters:
        test - An Expression to set the getOperator() method equal to.
        ifTrue - An Expression to set the getFirst() method equal to.
        ifFalse - An Expression to set the getSecond() method equal to.
        Returns:
        A BinaryExpression that has the ExpressionType property equal to Conditional and the getFirst() and getSecond() methods set to the specified values.
